  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Evaluating responses is a complex skill in itself.",
    "It requires students to compare responses by AI to scientifically or expertly grounded responses, and to evaluate how relevant the AI responses are to the context of the problem.",
    "From a future perspective, designing AI that can fully participate as an agent in social learning activities and fine-tune existing language models for educational purposes is not an adequate approach.",
    "According to Sharples (2023), current AI technologies lack, for example, 'long-term memory, the ability to reflect on its output and consolidate its knowledge from each conversation.",
    "More fundamentally, it does not capture the affective and experiential aspects of what it takes to be a learner and teacher' (p. 7)."
  ],
